CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1778767871
OL,3,CIs the 'd' in new station sign an
OL,4,Cupside down 'p'?
OL,6,FSome have said the characters are
OL,7,Fmisaligned and there has been
OL,8,Fspeculation over whether the "d" in
OL,9,F"Leeds" is an inverted "p".
OL,11,FA spokesperson for Leeds City Council
OL,12,Fsaid: "We are aware of a potential
OL,13,Fissue with Welcome to Leeds signage at
OL,14,FLeeds Train Station and we are in
OL,15,Fdiscussions with the relevant
OL,16,Fcontractors to ensure any error which
OL,17,Fis then identified is rectified by
OL,18,Fthem as soon as possible."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/5
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,370,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1778767871
OL,3,CIs the 'd' in new station sign an
OL,4,Cupside down 'p'?
OL,6,FSpeaking to ITV News outside the
OL,7,Fstation, one passenger said: "When I
OL,8,Flook, you can actually see that the
OL,9,F'd' is lower than the other letters."
OL,11,FAnother said: "I wouldn't have noticed
OL,12,Fhad I not been asked, but the 'e's'
OL,13,Fare slightly bigger than the body of
OL,14,Fthe 'd,' and I think that's why it
OL,15,Flooks a little bit odd."
OL,17,FOne woman said: "Is a 'p' not just an
OL,18,Fupside-down 'd' anyway?"
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/5
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
